ğŸ› ï¸ Assembly Notes

Use weatherproof enclosures with cable glands for all external cables.

Bearings should be lightly lubricated for long-term stability.

Shielded twisted pair cable reduces noise on long serial runs.

UV sensor requires a small UV-transparent cover (e.g., acrylic).

Align wind vane magnet precisely for accurate direction mapping.
